Tell HN: Microsoft Edge is browser with least learning curve from Chrome
text:
Chrome has been abusing there position from quite long. They are moving to Manifest V3, they don't support extensions on mobile and they disabled option to change webview.

Firefox is recommended choice to most people, but for some learning curve can be big(I tried to switch but failed several times). Reason might be performance, look and feel or devtools.

I found MS edge to be best candidate to switch from Chrome. It supports adblocker on mobile, has better privacy features, is as fast as chrome and has same devtools.
